body:
I have a weird bug, could also be a bug in GCC but I wanted to report it anyways.
Lately I upgraded my system and I got the new GCC 13.1.0. I was recompiling verilator after the update and I noticed weird errors on some of the designs.

```
package gpio_regblock_pkg;

    typedef struct {
        logic value;
    } GPIO_ODR__odr0_hwclr_cb852fb2_hwset_c201fea2__out_t;

    typedef struct {
        GPIO_ODR__odr0_hwclr_cb852fb2_hwset_c201fea2__out_t odr0;
    } __GPIO_ODR_odr0_226a8fa3_odr1_38ac8d61_odr10_2c841a0c_odr11_4989e4b2_odr12_ba5781f9_odr13_d2a5bdea_odr14_2f00530e_odr15_d473;


    typedef struct {
        __GPIO_ODR_odr0_226a8fa3_odr1_38ac8d61_odr10_2c841a0c_odr11_4989e4b2_odr12_ba5781f9_odr13_d2a5bdea_odr14_2f00530e_odr15_d473 odr;
    } gpio_regblock__out_t;
endpackage
```
Running this
```
verilator_bin --compiler gcc  -cc --Wno-fatal gpio_regblock_pkg.sv
```
I get this error
```
%Error: gpio_regblock_pkg.sv:16:9: syntax error, unexpected IDENTIFIER, expecting TYPE-IDENTIFIER
   16 |         __GPIO_ODR_odr0_226a8fa3_odr1_38ac8d61_odr10_2c841a0c_odr11_4989e4b2_odr12_ba5781f9_odr13_d2a5bdea_odr14_2f00530e_odr15_d473 odr;
      |         ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```
If I run the same thing with the same commit hash of verilator but compiled with GCC 12.1.0 it works without problems.

Now the problem is this string:
```
__GPIO_ODR_odr0_226a8fa3_odr1_38ac8d61_odr10_2c841a0c_odr11_4989e4b2_odr12_ba5781f9_odr13_d2a5bdea_odr14_2f00530e_odr15_d473
```
Originally it was longer but I cut it down to the 124 characters, and if I remove one character from the string it will compile.

What OS and distribution are you using?
Archlinux GCC 13.1.0

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
Sure I can try. But this might not be a Verilator problem at all, it could just be GCC.
But as I didn't notice any other problem with my system apart from this, I report it here.

I will compile GCC from source on Ubuntu tomorrow and will see if its only arch
